# Store reviewer accounts + static sign-in code

When writing **store/channel tester instructions / review notes / demo-account
credentials** for any platform, use the facts below. **Do not ask the user for
this again** — it is fixed.

## Reviewer accounts

- Emails: `reviewer@reversion.app` (primary), plus `reviewer1@reversion.app`
  … `reviewer5@reversion.app` for parallel reviewers.
- Any `@reversion.app` email is auto-flagged `is_review_account = true` (and
  `special_access = true`) in the backend, which **bypasses the entitlement
  gate** — so these accounts see real content instead of an empty home.

## Static sign-in code (no email sent)

- Sign-in is **passwordless email-code**. For any reviewer account, the login
  code is the fixed value **`4TGW6D`** (`MOBILE_REVIEW_FIXED_CODE`).
- Entering `4TGW6D` always works and **sends no email** — reviewers don't need
  inbox access.

## Roku-specific activation (on-device email-code sign-in)

- Roku does **not** use QR/code pairing (cert prohibits off-device linking). On
  the `SignInScreen`, the reviewer enters email `reviewer@reversion.app`, then the
  code **`4TGW6D`** on the on-screen keyboard. No phone, no website needed.
- Other platforms (Fire TV / Android TV / Tizen / Apple TV) use Welcome → Sign In
  → pairing code + QR → `reversion.app/activate`, then the same reviewer email +
  `4TGW6D`.

## Why this matters

- A **brand-new** account has no content by design and shows the "Nothing here
  yet" empty state. Reviewers who create their own account think the app is
  broken — **always tell them to use the reviewer credentials above and not
  create a new account.**

## Source of truth

- Backend: `is_review_account` / `special_access` flags + `MOBILE_REVIEW_FIXED_CODE`
  in the `reversion` repo. If these values ever change there, update this rule.
